{"author":{"id":"ae924cad0eccd510bd7c1844896b3dcc00e7daa039003bd9719a515e70528ab9"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1491248380,"nonce":"NEGAXPRgjywqmP1poO4LBxceKqo=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI5MTI1MDk3OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1226#issuecomment-291250978"},"message":"Now it does not make sense because \"This experiment is\" dropdown is now irrelevant.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1491325008,"nonce":"tcZz38Ia2ri7MB4+4dXto8LhuV4=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI5MTU2NDAxMg==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1226#issuecomment-291564012"},"message":"Here is a summary of our discussion with @gregvonkuster today:\n\n- there will be no single/multiple input select\n- interface with start with single condition (a repeat) containing two drop-downs: (1) for signal BAM dataset and (2) for optional control dataset. Each of the inputs (signal and control) will itself be a repeat allowing for multiple signal and control replicates with a single condition.\n\nGalaxy will process the tool form to always generate a [control file](http://lugh.bmb.psu.edu/software/multigps/example.design). In the simplest possible case (one signal and one control) the control file will look like this:\n\n```\nsignal_1_file  signal   BAM  1  1\ncontrol_file   control  BAM  1\n```\n\nwhen you have multiple signal replicates it will look like this:\n\n```\nsignal_1_file  signal   BAM  1  1\nsignal_2_file  signal   BAM  1  2\ncontrol_file   control  BAM  1\n```\n\nwhen you have multiple conditions with multiple replicates it will look like this:\n\n```\ntal1_signal_1_file    signal   BAM  Tal1   1\ntal1_signal_2_file    signal   BAM  Tal1   2\ntal1_control_file     control  BAM  Tal1\ngata1_signal_1_file   signal   BAM  Gata1  1\ngata1_signal_2_file   signal   BAM  Gata1  2\ngata1_control_file    control  BAM  Gata1\n```\n\nHowever, there are several questions for @shaunmahony:\n\n- when `Experiment type for this replicate: chipseq/chipexo.` is not chosen, what is the default?\n- `Fixed per-base read count limit for this replicate.` If this is set to be defined by user, the user should enter an integer, right?\n- can replicate number be optional for signal of there is only one replicate? \n\n\n![img_20170404_111657](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4291636/24665457/6bdbe37a-192b-11e7-8668-75e7ff804b5a.jpg)","files":null}]}